<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1872-03-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1872-03-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="58" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d58">
                        <head>No. 58.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Partridge</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                        of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-03-22"><hi rend="italic">March</hi> 22,
                                1872</date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 34.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your dispatch, No. 33, of the 22d of
                            January last, relating to the return of destitute citizens of the United
                            States in Brazil to this country has been received.</p>
                        <p>As you were informed in my dispatch No. 16, there is no appropriation
                            from which a sum to defray the passage of these persons to the United
                            States can properly be drawn.</p>
                        <p>A naval vessel is expected soon to return from Brazil, on which some of
                            them can embark, under orders heretofore issued.</p>
                        <p>I am, &amp;c,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>